Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000001_01:
This is the world you call home.
But, as you are out for a walk...
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000001_03: Use this and you'll stand a chance against those monsters!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000001_04: Donning the equipment, you feel an inexplicable surge of power begin to well forth!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000001_05: I'm surrounded! You over there, help me out!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000002_01: Thanks for saving me back there! Are you a hunter purrchance? I'm a Felyne.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000002_02: ...M-Meow?! What's that you've got in your paws?
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000002_03: A "smartphone," huh? I see... I bet you can get a good look around with something that handy.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000003_01: Something's falling from the sky! I-Is that...a person?!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000003_02: Hm... I haven't a clue why, but it looks like our world has been...connected with this one?
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000003_04: ...I think I have an idea of what's going on now. My name's Qualily. I serve the guild as a guide for hunters.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000003_05: What's that? There's no such thing as hunters, never mind guilds in this world?!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000003_06: ...Yet in spite of that, you managed to take down a pack of Jagras on your own? You're quite the catch!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000003_07: How'd you like to become a hunter under my supervision? We can also investigate the anomalies taking place while we're at it!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000004_01: Come on now, don't disappoint me like that.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000005_01: Much appreciated! It'll be reassuring to have someone familiar with this world on board.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000006_02: M-Meoooow!! That monster's even bigger than the ones from before!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000006_03: A Great Jagras, huh? A bit stronger than your average Jagras...but a fine opponent for our novice hunter here, I'd say!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000006_04: Just make sure to get out of the way of its rolling attack, then strike while it's unaware!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000007_01: Way to go taking down a Great Jagras like that!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000007_02: Aha... I knew you had what it took!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000007_03: Keep up this pace and climb the ranks to HR 11—only then can you consider yourself a true hunter.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000008_01: And to make sure you reach that goal, let's have our Felyne friend here act as your Palico.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000008_02: What's a Palico, you ask? One who supports your hunts and takes care of your daily needs—a reliable partner, in other words.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000008_03: And with that, I look forward to working with you, Hunter! I'll be showing you the ropes until you find your feet!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000008_04: While you lot are doing that, I'll be doing my best to learn what I can about this world.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000008_05: After all, wherever I look, there's things I'd never even imagined could exist... Oho, where to begin...!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000008_06: There's no stopping Qualily when she gets that sparkle in her eye... So, let's do what we can to pump up your hunter rank!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000009_01: ...That "smartphone" device is truly something... It must be the work of some master smith, just look at the... *mumble, mumble*
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000009_03: ...O-Oh, it's you two. So you've finally made it this far—much faster than I'd anticipated, might I say.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000009_04: It's time to take on your first 2★ monster. This will be a challenge unlike anything you've faced so far.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000009_06: If you can overcome this final trial, you can consider yourself a real hunter.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000010_01: I knew you had it in you... I hereby formally recognize you as a true hunter!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000011_01: Now, without further ado, let's have you finally begin to investigate the strange goings-on in this world.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000011_02: Our ultimate goal is to resolve the dimensional anomalies.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000011_03: So to achieve that, let's begin with an ecological investigation of the monsters that appeared in this world, slaying them as you go.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000011_04: Maybe in gaining an understanding of the monsters' activities, we can discover the truth behind what's going on.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000011_05: ...Plus, we might be able to find a way back to our own world.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000011_06: Hear, hear to that! Let's purress on together!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000012_01: Th-The King of the Skies! This is a cat-astrophe!!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000012_02: To think even a Rathalos would make an appearance...
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000012_03: The destructive power of its flames is nothing to scoff at... But as you are now, I know you stand a chance.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000012_04: There's no time to lose: slay that Rathalos!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000013_01: Astounding work! You've proven to me that you have the courage of a true hunter.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000013_02: But did you see how that Rathalos appeared from that portal right after the sky lit up...?
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000013_03: That can only mean that we too must have come to this world in the same way...
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000013_04: Not only that, but as long as those rifts exist, there'll be no end to the monsters.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000013_05: So we're going to need to figure out just what's causing those portals to appear.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000013_06: And for that, I'll be counting on your continued cooperation more than anything, Hunter!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000014_01: What's this?! There's pumpkins all over the place!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000014_02: Meow? And to top it off, everyone looks like they're in high spirits?
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000014_03: Heheh. This, my fine, furry friend, is the festival known over here as "Halloween".
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000014_04: A fur-stival? Now that sounds like a good way to let off some steam, right, Hunter? Let's go!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000015_01: Indeed... It seems that in this world, they have fun by wearing pumpkins on their head.
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000015_02: Ahhh, pumpkins: truly the most versatile of all veggies! You can eat 'em, decorate with 'em, equip 'em as armor...
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000015_03: Hunter! Let's get one on that head of yours right now and bring this party to life!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000016_01: Phew... I'm pooped. But, we got a good haul thanks to your purrseverance!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000016_02: Heh, looks like pumpkins are in full harvest over here, too. Say, you two: boiled or roasted, how'd you like them? Oh, but soup's surely the way to go...
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000016_03: Qualily looks like she's having a good time, and I'm having a blast, too! What about you, Hunter? A "Happy Halloween" for all!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000018_01: That cautiousness of yours would serve you well as a hunter!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000019_01: C'mon, think it over a bit?
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000020_01: You'd make a reaaaally great hunter, you know!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000022_01: You really want to stand around talking all day?
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000023_01: I can see it, clear as day! You! Out in the wilds! HUNTING!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000025_01: Hoh, you're a tough catch, I'll give you that!
Conversation.TALK_SCENE_000026_01: Such unbreakable resilience... You truly are a natural-born hunter!

MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_ANJANATH:
Infamous for its belligerence, this brute wyvern indiscriminately attacks all without hesitation.

The large membrane extending from its waist to the base of its tail fans out when it becomes agitated.

This fan-like membrane is thought to be used not only for intimidation, but also as a mode of body temperature control. This is attributed to the fact that when Anjanath expels flames from its mouth, the membrane has been spotted expanding in tandem, releasing excess heat.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_AZURE_RATHALOS:
A subspecies of Rathalos bearing a blue-colored shell.

It boasts far greater mobility than a normal Rathalos, relying on fierce aerial attacks to catch its prey unawares.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_BARNOS:
A ferocious type of wingdrake.

Regardless of size, should another monster enter their territory, they will weaken the intruder with a unique type of acid, before assaulting it as a group.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_BARROTH:
Perhaps in order to shield itself from hot temperatures, this monster is most often seen lurking beneath pools of mud.

It has also been known to use the mud it cloaks itself in as a means of attacking, so exercise caution.

Somewhat fastidious about its swamp, should the marsh be disturbed in any way, it will rush with reckless abandon towards the perpetrator.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_BLACK_DIABLOS:
Female specimen whose entire body has turned black in preparation for the mating season.

The dark black tone of their carapace acts as a warning color to other monsters, belying the unusually aggressive nature of this monster compared to its regular counterpart.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_DIABLOS:
A desert-dwelling monster feared for its ferocity.

Two distinctive, twisted horns protrude from its skull.

Fiercely territorial, it uses its remarkable hearing to sense overhead intruders while burrowed underground, attacking them without discrimination.

In spite of this, it is a strict herbivore, primarily feeding on desert cacti.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_GREATGIRROS:
This carnivorous monster prowls its territory, seeking out prey.

It takes down its target using the paralytic toxins secreted from its large fangs.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_GREATJAGRAS:
The leader of a pack of Jagras.

Renowned for their voracious appetite, they will mercilessly assault even monsters higher up in the food chain.

The sight of it devouring its prey whole is one to behold.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_JAGRAS:
A small monster that hunts in packs.

It is characterized by its outer hide and the large spines on its back, which are colored in such a way as to provide camouflage in forests. Should one of its allies be chased away, they will all retreat en masse.

If their territory is encroached by a large monster, they will assess the situation from a distance, attacking as a group only if they sense they are in danger.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_JYURATODUS:
A piscine wyvern that makes its habitat in muddy swamps. It has a tendency to use mud as a means by which to both camouflage itself and hunt with.

It is believed that they coat themselves with mud in order to restore moisture to their scales, which grow brittle and inhibit cutaneous respiration when dehydrated.

Exercise caution should you come across the mud which Jyuratodus spits out, as its high viscosity can easily restrict body movement.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_KULUYAKU:
A bird wyvern adept at grasping objects with its well-developed forelegs.

There have been sightings of it plundering eggs from other monsters, but it will often drop them in surprise if attacked.

When engaged in battle, it has a propensity to unearth sturdy rocks which it then uses as a weapon or shield.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_LEIGIANA:
This monster has been witnessed in swamp regions, tracking down the herds of Raphinos it preys upon.

It hunts by emitting freezing-cold air, which allows it to slow down its target.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_MERNOS:
A wingdrake with an appetite for berries.

When startled, Mernos will retreat together as a flock to find a safer location.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_NOIOS:
A wingdrake that reacts with a bloodcurdling scream when disturbed.

Ravenous by nature, they are commonly witnessed gathering around hunks of meat.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_PAOLUMU:
A flying wyvern capable of storing large quantities of air within its body.

By powerfully exhaling this air, it can travel afloat across the skies, delivering crushing blows with its hard tail.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_PINK_RATHIAN:
A variant of Rathian whose shell is tinted with a vivid, cherry-colored hue.

Brandishing its venom-laden tail with greater finesse than a common Rathian, it hunts by weakening its prey before finishing them off.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_PUKEIPUKEI:
A bird wyvern whose body contains a poisonous fluid.

It ensnares its prey by brandishing its whip-like tongue, which can be expanded and contracted at will.

By mixing the berries and plants it consumes with the venom in its body, it can release a devastating poison breath attack.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_RAPHINOS:
A wingdrake that always coordinates as part of a group.

Larger predators very often take advantage of this when targeting them as prey.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_RATHALOS:
A fearsome flying wyvern who has earned the moniker "King of the Skies."

Together with its female counterpart, it forms its territory around their nest, keeping close watch from above.

With its powerful wings, it swiftly descends to intercept any trespassers, assailing them with its mighty, poisonous claws.

In addition, it is well known for its ability to breathe fire.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_RATHIAN:
Known by the alternative name of "Queen of the Land."

With its outstanding leg strength, it hurtles across the land, subduing prey with its venom-laden tail.

It has occasionally been spotted hunting together with its male counterpart, Rathalos.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_SHAMOS:
A monster that dwells in dark places.

Sightings of them challenging hostile foes as a pack are not uncommon.
MonsterDescription.MONSTER_DESCRIPTION_TOBIKADACHI:
A fanged wyvern that darts around the thickets of its forested nest.

It generates static electricity by brushing its fur across the ground and nearby trees.
When a sufficient amount of friction has been built up, it enters into an "electrified" state where its body hairs begin to emit light and stand on end. Be especially wary of its head and tail when it takes on this appearance.

MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_ANJANATH:
It will often employ bite attacks at close-range, while at a distance it will attempt to lunge at you with great leaps.

Utilizing the flame sac in its throat, it has been reported that it will release a scorching fire breath when enraged.

It is precisely during or following this move that the monster is left susceptible to attacks. Additionally, it can be toppled by breaking its feet. In doing so, its weak head can be safely targeted.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_AZURE_RATHALOS:
This monster spends a great deal of time in flight, unleashing barrages of attacks that produce wind pressure. Given this, it would be wise to prepare equipment that negates wind pressure beforehand.

If you spot it gathering strength in mid-air, this is a sign that it's about to expel a powered-up flame breath—avoid this at all costs by dodging to the left or right. This variant's regular flame breath should not be taken lightly either, as its fire boasts greater attack power and remains on the ground for far longer than that of a normal Rathalos.

In addition to the head and wings, the tip of the tail is also a weak point, so do your best to aim for it.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_BARROTH:
This monster is left open following its headlong rush attack, allowing for its weak forelegs to be targeted, or for it to be toppled by breaking its hindlegs.

This monster is also known to attack by strewing and flinging mud. As such, though fire-element weapons are effective against it, it may be wise to employ water-element attacks so as to remove the hardened mud that bolsters its defenses.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_BLACK_DIABLOS:
Upon mustering its strength, it will violently charge towards hunters with an onslaught of attacks. As such, those unaccustomed to hunting this monster ought to focus heavily on evasion.

On the contrary, experienced hunters will look for a chance to cancel its consecutive flurry of attacks by breaking its body parts.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_DIABLOS:
The sheer destructive power of its colossal horns and thrusts from underground should not be taken lightly.

However, they also leave this monster susceptible to counter-attacks. Carefully sneak around it and try to aim for its vulnerable stomach.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_GREATGIRROS:
Using the paralytic fluid in its fangs, as well as its paralyzing breath, it is adept at immobilizing would-be hunters.

However, given its propensity towards moving in straight lines, well-timed evades to the left or right can allow for a counter-attack to its vulnerable head.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_GREATJAGRAS:
Making use of its expanding stomach, it boldly attempts to trap hunters by rolling on top of them.

By focusing your assault on its stomach, it will promptly empty the contents of it, leaving the monster in a stunned state where its weak head can be targeted.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_JYURATODUS:
Though the hardened mud that cakes its body renders attacks ineffective, this dirt can be scrubbed away using water-element weapons.

It relentlessly uses mud to its advantage by flinging or spitting it, as well as diving and lunging from within it, so try whittling down its stamina with attacks, or breaking its body parts in order to keep it above ground. Its head is its weak point.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_KULUYAKU:
There have been reported sightings of this monster utilizing dug-out boulders as a means of offense.

Given that frontal attacks will be met with this hard rock, it is advisable to strike from the side. However, its vulnerable forelegs and head can be broken in order to force it to drop its rock.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_LEIGIANA:
Veiled in frigid air, this monster is capable of a devastating onslaught of attacks. However, it leaves a small window of vulnerability after each assault, so try to determine when its attack combo has ended.

It has also been confirmed that poison is highly effective against this monster, preventing it from taking flight and emitting frost-coated attacks. The head is its weak point.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_PAOLUMU:
By deeply inhaling, it can suck in unwary hunters alongside large quantities of air.

Its inflated neck pouch can serve as a means by which to ground the beast if broken, allowing for its vulnerable head to be damaged.

Take caution, however, as some specimens are capable of unleashing a violent tornado breath attack.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_PINK_RATHIAN:
This subspecies displays different behavior compared to its regular counterpart, performing wild somersault attacks with its tail mid-flight.

It will also attempt to use its tail to sweep hunters off their feet, so it is imperative to judge which direction the tail is coming from before evading.

If it starts to move backwards while on the ground, this is a prelude to a powerful breath attack, so be sure to dodge to the left or right with good timing.

Its head and wings, as well as the tip of its tail are vulnerable, so focus your attacks on these body parts.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_PUKEIPUKEI:
This monster assails hunters with its poisonous saliva and extendable tongue.

After spitting out venom, it leaves a small opening in which its vulnerable head can be attacked.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_RATHALOS:
As implied by its title of "King of the Skies," this monster is capable of taking flight, whereupon it will attack from above with its flame breath.

By targeting its wings, or severing its tail, you may be able to force it to descend to the ground.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_RATHIAN:
The spikes that adorn this monster's tail are coated with a potent venom. However, this poison will be rendered ineffective should its tail be severed.

Its head is particularly vulnerable, so it would be wise to focus your aim on it during a hunt.
MonsterHint.MONSTER_HINT_TOBIKADACHI:
Deftly moving in all directions, it can stealthily launch unseen attacks from your blind spots.

The "electrified" state it enters into after accumulating friction can be canceled by breaking a body part, such as its head or tail.

Take advantage of the openings left by its tail slashes and gliding leaps to initiate a counter-attack.

Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00018: Hrrmeow... I just can't wrap my head around it—our world and this one being connected...
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00018_2: Buuuuut, with you around, I'm sure everything'll be fine!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00019: You took down Kulu-Ya-Ku, just as expected! ...I'm so purroud to be your manager!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00020: So Pukei-Pukei was no match for you, either, huh? Is this the power of my teachings...?
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00021: Well, it wasn't a "clean" match, what with all that dirt and mud...but victory is yours!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00021_2: By the way, you notice how the monsters just vanish into thin air once you beat 'em? I wonder where they disappear to...
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00022: The fact you've made it this far means your skills are the real deal... So my scouting talent must be the realest of all deals!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00023: Fine work! With someone of your caliber on board, I'm confident we can uncover the truth behind what's going on in this world!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00023_2: A job well done for my apurrentice!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00024: Even in the desert heat, you beat that tough monster without breaking a sweat! As expected of my appurrentice!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00024_2: M-Meow?! D-Did you see that flash in the sky just now?
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00025: I c-c-can't m-move!! B-B-But, your strength was even more s-s-stunning, Hunterrrrrr!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00025_2: Thanks to your investigation, we've confirmed the presence of a Great Girros in this world.
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00025_3: But the luminous phenomenon remains a mystery. Just what are those flashes of light...?
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00026: Paw-some stuff! Seems like you've really got the hang of hunting now!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00026_2: I see... So there were no unreported species confirmed in the forest region, huh?
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00026_3: Yet it was the very swamp where the flash was spotted that you came across Great Girros... There must be some connection between the monsters and the light.
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00027: You beat the monster, but my luggage was nowhere to be found. C-Could it have gobbled up all my delicious snacks...?
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00027_2: Wait, let's not jump to conclusions. I found some other tracks nearby.
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00027_3: Could the culprit, drawn in by the scent of food, have snatched the luggage from that Tobi-Kadachi?
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00028: We did it! My purrecious luggage!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00028_2: Time for a little snack I thi... M-Meow?! I-It's empty! M-My sweet, scrumptious mushrooooooms!!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00029: We've finally doled out payback for my dearly departed mushrooms! Revenge truly is a dish best served...fungal?
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00029_2: Did you two spot it? The very moment before that Jyuratodus appeared, a bright flash lit up the sky.
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00029_3: That light and the appearance of the monsters—I've no doubt that the two events are related. Keep an eye out for those flashes as you continue your search for monsters.
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00030: You took down Barroth! But those footprints seem to belong to a different m...
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00030_2: M-Meowchhh?! I-I-I feel like a cat on a hot tin roof! The ground's on fire!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00030_3: Those scorch marks are no doubt the work of a fire-breathing monster. Nice find, team!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00031: Incredible, you went toe-to-toe with that hothead!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00031_2: ...However, you were unable to encounter the flashes this time.
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00031_3: Perhaps the lights only appear at the exact moment the monsters appear?
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00032: It was a gruelling hunt, but we took out Rathian!!! And to top it off, we caught another glimpse of that big ol' flash in the sky!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00032_2: And you're not the only one who spotted it. It was an almost blinding light... Though that's the furthest I was able to analyze it.
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00032_3: No matter how many new monsters spawn, their total population doesn't seem to be increasing much. What could this mean...?
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00033_2: I knew it! The luminous phenomenon and the monsters' appearance are connected!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00033_3: Not only that, but the monsters seem to be gradually increasing in strength. If this keeps up...
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00034: You were seriously ameowzing out there, taking down that sandy roughneck like that!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00034_2: But, y'know...the fact that the monsters are getting this strong is giving me a real nasty feeling...
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00035: M-Meow?! The sky lit up just now!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00036: I just know you'll be able to get to the bottom of those weird portals! Let's figure this out together, partner!
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00036_2: Looks like this light will require further investigation. And for that, I'll be counting on your cooperation, Hunter.
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00036_3: Looks like this light will require further investigation. And for that, I'll be counting on your cooperation, Hunter.
Quest.CHAPTER_ED_MESSAGE_00037: Looks like these rifts will require further investigation. And for that, I'll be counting on your cooperation, Hunter.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00018: Those monsters have got us surrounded! But if you keep cool and follow my lead, we'll be fine! Now, ready your sword!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00019: To be recognized as a pro hunter, you're gonna need to work your socks off till HR 11!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00019_2: It'll be a cinch for you, though! And I'll be here to lend a paw!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00020: The only way to get tougher is to equip tougher weapons and armor! That's what being prepared is all about!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00021: Right then, time to see if you've done your homework! Take everything you've learned and kick some monster hide!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00022: You're only a few steps away from becoming an expert hunter! Hunt and gather till the goal!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00023: This is it: your final test... A 2★ monster! Give it your all!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00024: Right then, our newest hunter! Let's get straight into the investigation.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00024_2: First up on our list is the desert region. I'd like you to assess just what kinds of monsters have made their nest there.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00024_3: Let's have you begin with a survey of the desert region. Your first official mission will be to find out what kinds of monsters have begun to make their nest there.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00025: Earlier, I caught sight of some strange lights flashing around the swamp region. I'll need you to investigate this right away.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00026: Your next task will be an investigation of the forest habitat. What species of monsters lie in wait among the thickets, I wonder...?
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00027: M-Meow?! What a cat-astrophe! My luggage has disappeared! All my mushrooms and snacks... Gone!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00027_2: Your mushrooms? Sorry to hear about that. Who would do such a...
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00027_3: S-Such footprints?! I've never seen anything like these around here... They've got to belong to the perpetrator—after it!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00028: Incidentally, there were reported sightings of a "giant balloon" floating nearby the footprints we stumbled across.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00028_2: A "round and fluffy" balloon to be precise. With a description like that, there's only one monster that fits the bill: a Paolumu.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00028_3: I'll need you to investigate this matter further. Oh, and feel free to hunt down your furry friend's missing luggage while you're at it.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00029: Our culprit must be a real gourmand to have finished off every last bit of your Palico's food...
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00029_2: So, let's have you hone your search towards this kind of monster—one of the gluttonous variety.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00029_3: It's time to get your hands dirty. That's right: it's mushroom hunting time!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00030: Meow?! I've never seen footprints as big as this before!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00030_2: We might get a glimpse of that light again if we track down this monster! Let the hunt begin!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00031: Based on nearby witness reports, I'd say the prime suspect is none other than an Anjanath.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00031_2: I'll need an urgent investigation launched into tracking down that Anjanath. Pronto.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00032: The monsters, myself, and your Palico... Just how did we arrive in this world?
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00032_2: I firmly believe the answer to that lies in the lights. Please continue your investigation for the time being.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00033: You two! Another flash has been reported!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00033_2: If my hunch is right, then that means another monster's appeared. Investigate and slay it right away.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00034: Of all the...! We've just received word of a monster sighting: a Diablos, at that.
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00034_2: I'll need you to investigate and subdue it immediately!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00035: We've received reports of a flash brighter than anything witnessed to date!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00035_2: If our assumptions are true, then that can only mean a new monster has spawned. Make your way to the scene, posthaste!
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00036_2: This will be an opponent that lives up to its title, "King of the Skies." But as you are now, we might just stand a chance...
Quest.CHAPTER_OP_MESSAGE_00036_3: We've no time to lose: hunt Rathalos!

Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00058: Kulu-Ya-Ku might be seen as an opponent for rookie hunters, but that doesn't mean you should let your guard down!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00059: Pukei-Pukei has a nasty habit of spitting poison! Time your evades well to keep from getting hit!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00060: That's Barroth! You'll have trouble damaging its rock-hard head, so aim for those vulnerable forelegs instead!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00061: This Great Jagras looks like less of a pushover than the last one you hunted... Now's the chance to purrove your growth as a hunter!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00062: M-Meow?! It's Kulu-Ya-Ku! Purrform some slick sideways dodges to avoid its lethal jump attack!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00063: This monster's fangs are dripping with a paralyzing toxin! One bite and you'll be immobilized, so don't let it catch you!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00064: Even out here in the darkness of the woods, Kulu-Ya-Ku sure does stick out like a sore thumb! Watch its movements and dodge accordingly!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00065: Watch out for Pukei-Pukei's venomous saliva! Observe its movements carefully, then get out of the way of incoming attacks!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00066: This beast generates static electricity with its fur, and swiftly leaps around like a wild lightning bolt! Keep your guard up or you're in for a shock!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00067: That Kulu-Ya-Ku looks a good deal stronger than the one from before... But when it comes to strength, you're number one, Hunter!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00068:
Don't be tricked into thinking it's some cute big balloon! Once Paolumu gets peeved off, it'll—
...M-Meow! Incoming!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00069: Here comes Barroth! ...And this one's in an even worse mood than usual. Time to send this grumpy lunk packing!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00070: H-How dare you eat MY mushrooms! Let's give this monster a taste of vengeance!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00071: Pukei-Pukei's on an even wilder rampage than before! All the more reason for you to stay calm and watch its movements closely!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00072: Ick! What a mess! Time your dodges well if you don't want your lovingly-forged armor caked in muck!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00073: Here it comes—the Relentless Ruffian! Watch out for its searing flame breath, or you'll end up like a Well-Done Steak!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00074: You again?! How many times must we... Uh-oh, it's got its trusty rock in hand—looks like this one’s serious!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00075: That’s the Queen of the Land, Rathian! If that poison-laced tail hits you, you’re in for a world of pain!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00076: Uh-oh! Paolumu’s beginning to inhale for its breath attack! Don't let it blow you off course!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00077: A...a-achooooo! *sniff* Legiana's chilling breath will fur-eeze you to the bone if it hits!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00078: M-M-Meeeowch! Avoid those two big, thick horns—unless you feel like becoming a skewered snack!
Quest.URGENT_QUEST_MESSAGE_00079: They don't call this guy "King of the Skies" for nothing, but you've got this, Hunter! Brace yourself!

SkillDescription.SPECIAL_ATTACK_GREATSWORD: Gathers all of the body's strength into a devastating slash attack. (Power: {effect_amount_2}%)

Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_ARMOR_SKILL_1: Once an armor piece has been upgraded to Grade 2, useful skills inherent to that armor will be unlocked. As long as this armor is equipped, the relevant skill's effect will activate during a hunt.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_ARMOR_SKILL_2: The types of skills which each armor grants differs depending on the piece. Some may impart stat boosts, while others unlock or strengthen actions during a hunt.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_ARMOR_SKILL_3: By tapping the skill's icon, you can get a detailed explanation of each skill's effect. Try out each skill to turn the tide of a hunt in your favor!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_BOOST_BATTLE_REWARD_1: Using a Special Carving Knife or Gems, you can double the number of materials rewarded from a hunt. This is especially recommended when rare materials or materials you've been searching for are dropped.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_BOOST_BATTLE_REWARD_2: Tap here and you can try out a Special Carving Knife for free just this once to DOUBLE your rewards!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_CAMERA_2: Let's get right to it then!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_CAMERA_3: Start by dragging the screen with one finger—that way, you can check out your surroundings.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_CAMERA_4: Paw-some! I wonder what'll happen if you try pinching the screen with two fingers?
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_CAMERA_5: Oh, so that lets you zoom out, giving you a nice bird's-eye-view of the map!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_CAMERA_6: Hey, I couldn't help but notice, but...what's that you've got in your paws?
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_CAMERA_7: A "smartphone," huh...? I bet you can get a good look around with something that handy!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_DELIVERY_ITEM_QUEST_1: This type of quest requires you to find and turn in specific items. Quest items can be acquired either by gathering in the field or as rewards for slaying monsters.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_DELIVERY_ITEM_QUEST_2: Quest items have no purpose outside of completing the relevant quest, so any leftover quest items will be removed from the inventory upon completion.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_ELEMENT_1: Weapons imbued with elements that monsters are weak to will inflict more damage. Try switching your weapon to exploit the monster's weakness.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_ELEMENT_2: Strategy is key, Hunter! Make sure to check a monster's weakness before you dive in.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_ELEMENT_3: Tap here and you can change your weapon to one of an effective element!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EMERGENCY_QUEST_1: Urgent Quests may pop up as you purrogress in your adventure. Tough monsters will appear, so make sure you're ready!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EMERGENCY_QUEST_2: Urgent Quests may pop up as you purrogress in your adventure. Tough monsters will appear, so make sure you're ready!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_FORGE_1: You've managed to collect loads of monster materials from your hunts! How about we try forging some equipment?
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_FORGE_2: When new equipment can be forged, they'll be added here.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_FORGE_3: First of all, go ahead and make a Jagras Edge!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_FORGE_4: Some equipment have elemental properties! You can deal more damage to monsters that are weak to that element!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_FORGE_5: Meow... Looks like Great Jagras materials are needed to make a Jagras Edge.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_FORGE_6: Now, tap on the Forge button to start smithing!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_FORGE_7: Nice job! Jagras Edge is a water-element weapon, meaning it's a purrfect match against Kulu-Ya-Ku.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_FORGE_8: Keep on collecting monster materials so we can forge all kinds of new goodies. Oh, and don't fur-get to upgrade them, either!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_1: Begin by tapping the Equipment button!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_10: There are many fur-ightening monsters in the world. If you're having a hard time, try upgrading your equipment!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_11: You can also tap here to check your armor sets.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_12: Firstly though, let's try upgrading your weapon.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_2: This is where you can view and upgrade your equipment.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_3: A green arrow means that the equipment can be strengthened. Let's try upgrading it!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_4: You can confirm the status of your equipment here.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_5: Tap this button to visit the upgrade screen.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_6: Here, you can get a sneak preview of how much stronger the equipment will be when upgraded.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_7: And here, the materials needed for upgrading are shown!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_8: Tap the "Level Up" button to complete the upgrade!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_9:
Congratulations!
Your equipment has leveled up!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_EQUIPMENT_UPGRADE_EXPERT_: Equipment which have been upgraded to their maximum level can be upgraded even further via Overgrading. Once overgraded to Grade 2, beneficial skills useful for hunting may be unlocked.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_FRIEND_LIST_1: By adding someone as a friend, you can view each other's HR and equipment, as well as the number of times you've gone on a hunt together.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_FRIEND_LIST_2: While hunting together with a friend, whenever you use recovery items, your friend will also be healed by a small amount.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_FRIEND_LIST_3: If you use a referral code to invite a friend to the game, both of you will receive gifts.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_MARKED_MONSTER_2: Your Palico will automatically use Paintballs to mark surrounding monsters you can hunt later. Palico Paintballs are replenished once a day. *Adventure Sync must be enabled.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_MARKED_MONSTER_3: Your Palico will acquire items from surrounding small gathering points. When the bag is full, no more items can be collected. You can claim the items when you reopen the app. *Adventure Sync must be enabled.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_MARKED_MONSTER_4: By using a Paintball yourself, you can mark any monster of your choosing encountered in the field.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_MELDING_POT_1: Decorations can now be attached to equipment of grade 3 and above. By attaching one, a designated skill will be granted. They can be made via melding pots.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_MELDING_POT_2: You can create decorations by melding various materials together with rarestones, which can be obtained from 3★ or above monsters. Be aware that the melding process takes time to complete.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_MULTI_BATTLE_1: You can hunt alongside nearby players, with a maximum party size of 4 hunters.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_MULTI_BATTLE_2: By tapping "Hunt with nearby hunters" in the hunt preparation screen, hunters in the vicinity can be recruited to join your hunt.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_MULTI_BATTLE_3: If a nearby hunter is seeking comrades, an invitation message will be displayed in the home screen. Try cooperating with other hunters!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_PALICO_BAG_1: Even while the game is running in background mode, your Palico will collect items for you from gathering points in your vicinity. *Adventure Sync must be enabled.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_PALICO_BAG_3: I got my paws on some nearby items while you weren't looking. Make sure to claim 'em!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_PALICO_BAG_4: The more you walk about, the more stuff I'll pick up, so keep on exploring!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_PARTY_1: You can now form parties with friends and nearby hunters. The maximum number of hunters you can have in a party is 4.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_PARTY_2: You can either create your own party or scan a QR code to join other hunters' parties.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_PARTY_3: You can invite party members by tapping "Invite Party" from the hunt preparation menu. Any group hunts started while in a party will be conducted together with your party members.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_QUEST_10: And with that, here's your reward for slaying the pack of Jagras earlier.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_QUEST_2: Complete quests by undertaking tasks such as slaying monsters and gathering materials.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_QUEST_3: As you progress through the prologue story, your hunter rank (HR) will increase, unlocking a variety of features.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_QUEST_5: Keep it up and aim to become a pro hunter!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_QUEST_6: I've put together a bunch of quests purrfect for rookie hunters like you to take on, so let's have a look!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_QUEST_7: Work your way through each objective and purrogress through the quests!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_QUEST_8: Here's a little purresent for saving my skin earlier!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_QUEST_9: ...You've got a look on your face like you're not sure what to do next. How about we start off with an introduction to quests?
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_RESOURCE_POI_1: Let's try upgrading our equipment so we can fight even more fur-midable foes!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_RESOURCE_POI_2: You can get materials to upgrade your equipment from gathering points like this! Tap them to gather items.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_RESOURCE_POI_3:
If you miss something, don't worry!
I'll retrieve it for you!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_RESOURCE_POI_4: Okay, now we can upgrade your equipment. Let me show you the ropes!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_RESOURCE_POI_5: Also, keep an eye out for big gathering points, where you can get your paws on a lot of items!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SEASON_QUEST_1: Season stories will be available only for a limited period of time. When a season story ends, a new one will begin, so do your best to complete the story while it's available.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SEASON_QUEST_4: You've finally become a full-fledged hunter! From now on, Hunter Rank Points can be gained by slaying large monsters and completing Special Quests.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_10: I haven't the foggiest why, but it looks like our world and this one have become connected in some way...
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_11: Say, which guild do you hail from, hunter? What's that?! You're not a hunter? Well now's as good a time as any to start!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_12: I've put together a bunch of quests purrfect for rookie hunters like you to take on, so let's have a look!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_13: Here's a little purresent for saving my skin earlier!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_14: I know! How about I become your Palico to help you get on your feet?
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_15:
This is the world you call home.
But, as you are out for a walk...
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_16:
"You over there, save me!"
A cat-like creature, surrounded by a horde of monsters, beckons to you for help.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_17:
"Use that and you'll stand a chance!"
The furry creature frantically gestures towards the weapon at your feet.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_18:
"Put this on, too!"
Donning the armor passed to you, you feel an inexplicable surge of power welling forth from within.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_19: Thanks for getting rid of those monsters! Are you purrchance a hunter? I'm a Felyne.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_20: ...M-Meow? What's that you've got in your paws there?
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_21: A "smartphone," huh? I see, I see... That looks like it could come in handy!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_22: Maybe we could use it to try get a good look at our surroundings.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_4: Take care of the rest of 'em!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_7: M-Meow! D-Don't eat me, monsters, you'll be coughing up hairballs! You over there, lend me a paw!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SMALL_MONSTER_9: Thanks for getting me out of that tight spot! You beat those monsters without even breaking a sweat!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_ABOUT_SPECIAL_SKILL_1: Once a weapon has reached Grade 2, powerful techniques unique to each weapon type will be unlocked. Build up the Special Gauge with attacks and tap the Special Skill button to unleash them.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_1: Well, now that you've got the hang of looking around... M-M-Meow?!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_10:
And so it goes, even in this world:
Where monsters appear, a hunter is needed.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_11: I have a request. In order to deal with the monsters and unravel the strange events taking place here...I'd like you to become a hunter.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_12: What? Sorry, I didn't quite catch that.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_13: My thanks. Being unfamiliar with this world, your cooperation is a great reassurance.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_2:
While taking in the lay of the land, a bright light suddenly flashes above you.
"S-Something's falling from the sky!"
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_3:
Just before hitting the ground, the mysterious falling object shifts its posture to allow for a graceful landing.
"M-Meow?! It couldn't be...?!"
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_4: That which had descended from the sky was none other than a person—a person dressed like no one you had ever seen before.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_5: Hm... By some twist of fate, it looks like our world has been connected with this one.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_7: So that's where you'd gotten off to. And the one next to you is...a local hunter?
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_8: The cast of characters which had abruptly revealed themselves before you—the monsters, the Felyne, and Qualily—appear to all hail from another world.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_APPEARANCE_GUILD_MASTER_9: Over there, the task of tracking down and slaying monsters falls on the shoulders of those known as "hunters."
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_FAILED_EXPERT_1: If you're struggling to win, try upgrading your weapons and armor.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_10: Tap here to use a recovery item. I'll keep you stocked up while you're a rookie, so don't hesitate to use 'em!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_11: M-Meow?! Looks like their boss has shown up! Take it down just like the others!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_12: Without even realizing it, you have found yourself embarking on the path to becoming a pro hunter. Despite a sense of trepidation, the support of the Palico at your side puts you at ease.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_13:
Cutting short your conversation, a mysterious light begins to shine once more...
"M-Meow?! What is it this time?!"
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_14: Without warning, a monster several times larger than those from before appears in front of you. Uh-oh... And it seems it's noticed you!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_15: Way to go, knocking out that big lunk! Stick with me and you'll be an expurrt hunter in no time flat!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_16: Oh I fur-got to ask: you're not hurt, are you? Just in case, let's get you patched up real quick!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_17: A Great Jagras?! Though it pains me to say, I’m in no state for battle... So how about we use this as an opportunity to test your skills?
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_18: This’ll be a piece of cake for our Jagras-slaying fur-iend here!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_19: Go on, Hunter, tap that monster!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_20: Way to go taking down a Great Jagras like that!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_21: An impressive performance indeed. Keep up the hard work as a rookie, and aim for Hunter Rank 11.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_22: If you can manage that, then I can officially recognize you as a full-fledged hunter.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_24: With the support of your knowledgeable Felyne friend, who will act as your "Palico", continue completing quests on the journey to reaching Hunter Rank 11.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_3: Large monsters will glow red before attacking. Flick right, left, or down to evade their attack.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_4: If the monster's health can be fully depleted within the time limit, the hunt will end in success. If it cannot be reduced to 0, you will fail the hunt.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_6: Think you've got the hang of hunting and completing quests? Keep it up!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_7: If a monster's attack causes your health to reach 0, you will faint. Be prepared to dodge attacks when the monster glows red!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_8: Your health will automatically replenish over time. However, you can also use recovery items to recover quickly. First-Aid Meds will be supplied in limited quantities for free once a day.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BATTLE_LARGE_MONSTER_9: Even if your health is fully depleted, you can continue the hunt by using recovery items. *First-Aid Meds will be prioritized.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BEGIN_SECOND_ROUND_QUEST_1: Upon completing the final quest of the main story, the campaign can be restarted from the beginning an indefinite number of times.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_BEGIN_SECOND_ROUND_QUEST_2: With each successful lap of the season story, the difficulty of both regular quests and Urgent Quests will rise, and monsters in the field will grow stronger. Continue seeking greater challenges!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_DURING_BATTLE_SKILL_LOCKON: Try using the Lock On skill!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_DURING_BATTLE_SPECIAL_SKILL_1:
Tap the button to perform a Special Skill!
Invulnerability granted while performing
Tutorial.SENTENCE_DURING_BATTLE_SWORD_SHIELD_1:
Long press to perform a Hold Action!
Sword & Shield: Guard
Tutorial.SENTENCE_HOW_TO_JOIN_QR_CODE_1: Marked monsters can be hunted together with other hunters by sharing a QR code with them.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_HOW_TO_JOIN_QR_CODE_2: Tap the QR code scan button in the upper-right corner of the Paintball List to activate the camera app. Nearby hunters can then scan the QR code on your device.
Tutorial.SENTENCE_INTRODUCTION_BATTLE_1: Let's learn some basic combat controls. Follow my instructions!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_LIST_IN_MARKED_MONSTER_1: I went ahead and marked a monster for you! You can check it by tapping here!
Tutorial.SENTENCE_LIST_IN_MARKED_MONSTER_2: Marked monsters can be hunted whenever you want! ...Well, until they run away, at least. Keep an eye on each mark's expiry time!
